ture of javassist. Using `mvn dependency:get` could help since I have the POM. My goal is to output a single JSON object that includes all risks. \\n\\nFor potential actions, the no-action option emphasizes that OGNL is self-contained. It suggests that the Java test failure is due to assertion logic, not setup issues. I also need to clarify the agent guidance.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test setup for Forge workflow**\\n\\nThe user wants to avoid restating deterministic entries, so I can set up an empty string. However, if I skip the module opens, the agent might generate tests without the required `add-opens`, leading to failures. The existing scaffold already has JVM arguments. I need to figure out if the new library will inherit those or if it will cause an issue. The user's main concern is preparing a Forge workflow for a library issue that requires additional setup beyond the standard test scaffold. The OGNL scaffold may not include the necessary `add-opens`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating JDK arguments**\\n\\nI noticed that the project includes `-Dillegal-access=permit`, but this seems to be obsolete after JDK 17. There's also the `--illegal-access=permit` and `--add-opens` options to consider. The current build only mentions `java.lang`, and it has reached coverage with just one assertion failing. I need to think through whether it's necessary to update these arguments or if they will actually impact the functionality in the current setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java setup risks**\\n\\nI need to focus on the setup preparations if any advisory aspects come into play. JDK configuration can only happen through generated tests, which is a bit tricky. I should consider the risks related to the removal of SecurityManager APIs in JDK 25 and ensure tests don't depend on it. Plus, there's the concern about the `--illegal-access` option, which might be obsolete in JDK 17. It's quite a lot to keep track of!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"OGNL is a self-contained expression/reflection library with Javassist as a normal transitive dependency and no external service, but meaningful JDK 17+ reflection coverage needs test JVM module opens.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Configure generated OGNL tests to run with JVM args `--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED` and `--add-opens=java.base/java.util=ALL-UNNAMED`, matching OGNL 3.3.5's own JDK17+ test profile. Do not add Javassist manually: `ognl:ognl:3.3.5` already declares `org.javassist:javassist:3.29.0-GA` as a compile dependency. Avoid relying on successfully installing a `SecurityManager` on JDK 25; guard or skip assertions that require it.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The observed java run failure reproduces as an assertion/behavior issue in the existing tests, not as a missing dependency or Docker setup problem.\",\n    \"JDK 25 changes around deprecated `SecurityManager` and strong encapsulation can make older OGNL coverage tests brittle even when setup is correct.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0efa718c0d1deef5016a42384d115481938bc5199786b10501\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3877, "output": 1829, "cacheRead": 46080, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 51786, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782724661607, "responseId": "resp_0efa718c0d1deef5016a423836777c819385bb2d3c6e09a0e2"}, "toolResults": []}
